    "client_msg_id": "e37a5f81-3ac8-4da0-aee7-33c6d6951fef",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "One example that’s fairly terrible to use: Chrome Inspector + React DevTools. It’s terrible because\n(a) RDT is old and buggy, and much of the vital component metadata can be lost even in totally valid React programs (but fortunately there’s a new version that looks a lot better), and\n(b) although you _can_ use Chrome Inspector as your IDE of choice (yes, it lets you edit and save files), I can’t imagine that many people want to",
